<userid>100747167545283324316</userid><Name>Gautham N</Name><Date>1555736547313<//Date><rating>5<//rating>< review>
I had my appointment and arrived early by about 30 minutes, since I did take the VTA light rail to get there. Since my son accompanied me (and we didn't plan for it and hence no appointment for him), they treated him as walk-in. The receptionist asked me to have his name in the sign-in sheet just below mine and gave me the usual 30min-3hr wait spiel for walk-ins. However, we both got called 15m early and the agent (Cassandra) in there, was super helpful. She had my son application done online on my phone and got the procedure done in about 10 min for both of us. She even pointed me out to couple of lunch places around the joint. It was smooth and I'd recommend this place - but go with an appointment.

(on a different issue, faced a nightmare at the VTA LRT station on our return, with a crazy guy going off rails!)</review>

<review>Besides today, the last time I was there was about a year ago.
Now I remember why I don't go there.

1. When I walked in, it was EXTREMELY loud in there.
They had the volume on the television and/or the stereo really loud, and had to basically shout at each other to be heard over the music.
Apparently nobody there has the common sense to lower the volume, so you don't have to yell at each other to be heard.

2. They said the wait time on both occasions was between 1 1/2 to 2 hours for a haircut.

3. Both times I was there, most of the barbers were either on their phones or having lengthy conversations with one another or the clients. Very little hair cutting was taking place, which helps explain the 1 1/2 - 2 hour wait times.

Perhaps I may return again next year.
Maybe they will have improved by then....< /review></record>

<Name>Carly Lenderts</Name>< Time>
1360035672363< /Time>
<Rating>2</Rating>< Text>
Truly an awful experience. The website instructions are wrong, and it was very difficult to get in touch with anyone via phone to get the instructions and the forms. The background check from the FBI must be less than three months old, and if not you will have to get another one. The online form will not accept a large and odd range of words and characters, from the word "and" to a "/." If you enter any of the forbidden characters, it will delete the entire form and log you out. The consulate staff does not tell you this unless you email back about the form not accepting your information.

The pictures I sent in were wrong (which was probably my own fault) but they were very rude in demanding that I have new passport photos taken. The original fee for the student visa was $140, which I submitted with my original application in early July. When I called in mid-August to make sure my application was complete, I was told that it was. I was then called a week later and informed that the fee had changed on July 1 to $160 and that I must send $20 more. I did, the following business day, then sent an email saying the money was on its way. Two days later I received a very angry phone call from the woman who works at the consulate demanding to know where the money was. I explained to her that I had already emailed and the money should arrive the next day. She hung up on me.

FINALLY, one week before I was due to leave for Chile, I receive an email from her saying my visa is ready for me to pick up on Monday in Los Angeles. This was on a Thursday, and I live in Colorado and was planning to fly to LA the following Wednesday. She told me I'd have to change my flight because the consulate does not give out visas on Tuesdays or Thursdays. I cried the whole day, positive that I would have to cancel my whole semester abroad. Fortunately, my father managed to call her and convince her to give me an appointment for Friday morning.

Picking up my visa took LESS THAN five minutes! And she wanted me to spend hundreds of dollars changing my flight.

Sorry for writing a novel...
Point being: Getting a visa will be a royal pain. It is expensive and the bureaucracy is unbelievable. The staff is rude and difficult to reach. I never want to leave the country for more than 90 days ever again.</Text>

< Review>
I hired A+ Construction & Remodeling to remodel my kitchen in Spring 2021. We walked through what I had in mind, developed a design, made revisions, and chose materials all within a reasonable timeline. This process was expedited by their responsive communication with me via a convenient texting app, which I appreciated. Despite the difficulties presented by the pandemic in terms of scheduling work and managing appliance deliveries, their employees and subcontractors did their best. Any errors and miscommunications were addressed. They were efficient throughout and I didn't feel rushed. And most importantly, my finished kitchen looks brighter and the design is consistent, which were my main objectives.< /Review>

<Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
When my husband and I decided we wanted to remodel our kitchen we knew that we needed to find a good company to help us make our (ok more my) kitchen dreams come true.

From the first contact with A+, it was very easy and quick to get someone to come out. Mike was our estimator, and he came down to Vacaville on a Friday night to take measurements and get our ideas. Then we went up to their showroom to pick out options. We even had to push the remodel for a couple of months and A+ didn't harass or push us and when we were ready they got us on their schedule right away.

George was our foreman and he also came down to the house to check things out. I wanted a wall removed and George was the one who could say if it was load bearing or not-spoiler it wasn't!! He was always quick to answer texts and email - and gave input whenever we needed it. The designer that helped us finalize everything was awesome and even helped us adjust our island so we would have more seating around it.

The crews were always punctual and cleaned up after themselves. If there was ever a change on the schedule my husband and I were both contacted so we could make necessary adjustments. We had already replaced our floors, so the crew was very careful of them, and took the floors up and then reinstalled them, around our new kitchen. Once all the work was completed George came back to do a walk through with us and even showed my husband how we could adjust the drawers if we wanted too. The crew even leveled out our refrigerator doors for us!

I think the attached pictures truly show the quality work that A+ does!<//Text>

< text>
I came in here Sunday night and it was just awful. The water heater blew out (which can't be helped I know) which caused dishes to be scarce, but on top of that the food was very limited, and when they finally brought something out it was warm instead of hot. The options were just very slim. The floor was wet, some dishes were still dirty, the ice cream machine was also down. Just a horrible night and time. I wish they offered more variety, but it's the same every time I go. That with dinner costing $15 for what tastes like microwaved food? I'm good. Not worth it. I'm just going to go to Great Moon for my buffet options... Cheaper, more variety, less cramped environment.</text>

< review>
So I use to live in Tennessee, where it is known as old country buffet. I grew up on this place and their food, nothing but great nostalgia. What happened to their quality of food? While the food is warm and cooked, everything was either overcooked or overly salty. Maybe my tastes changed as I got older, or the food itself changed. Now I'm going to give them another chance, but I must admit that my last experience really put me off of their food. Also, I remember there use to be a meat carving section at the old country locations. Maybe it's just regional, but I do miss them.<//review>

< Name>
Rob B</Name>
< date>
1416938746022< /date>
<Rating>2</Rating>< text>
The staff is top notch friendly & helpful but the corporate office does not support the restaurant.  There is poor food planning.  On weekends they will run out of certain food products including the meat & poultry.  The bowl of new salad mix that was recently introduced is frequently empty.    The soup bar is not filled regularly & soup plates are not always available.  Many times you have to wait to collect your meal items because there are not enough plates, cups & utensils on hand at peak meal hours.  It appears the equipment is in disrepair as staff claims the dishwasher can not handle demand & the ice cream machine is malfunctioning.   Most of the time the ice cream machine is a dirty mess.   The beverage bar is out of ice & cups more times than acceptable.   The restaurant could use a makeover.  The lighting in dining area needs to be modernized.  The ceiling needs to be cleaned & brightened.  The open ceiling tiles need to be closed to keep the dirt & dust from circulating through the sub-ceiling into the dining area.  The walls need to be repainted a brighter color to make the place feel friendly & modern.   Some of the wall pictures need to be removed & updated.  This is not Horn & Hardart or Howard Johnsons.  In the warm months the management needs to do a better job keeping the mosquitoes out of the restaurant.  They hang at the front window area all day.  There is no bug control here. This restaurant's operation brings the chains reputation down & keeps away potential patrons.   If it wasn't for the reasonable prices & the frequent discounts offered most people would boycott this location.   The Bakersfield, CA  location is a model restaurant they should try to copy here.<//text>

Great discount for active/retired/veteran military personnel on Monday nights! Most discount coupons are are trivial at best, except Thursday nights kids eat for $1.99 with a paying adult (limit two kids per paying adult). When it was JJ North's, beverages were included with your meal.  I also liked JJ North's pocket menus!  When a beverage, or milk runs out, they are slow to adress it, if at all.
